Lady Naleena was my very first Eq character ever created.<br>
She was born about 3 weeks prior to Kunark's release.<br>
Around level 15 I became very frustrated with the resists I saw with my Rain spell and being new I thought it was being resisted because I wasn't a &quot;good&quot; magician. So, I took all the plat I had (about 10p) and &quot;twinked&quot; a wood elf druid.<br>
I thought she was &quot;twinked&quot; because she had all leather gear and all her level 1 spells.<br>
Time moves on and now the druid (level 50) is mostly a taxicab for my cleric.<br>
<br>
A friend brand new to Eq could not really play well with either the druid or the cleric so Lady Naleena returned to  Norrath once again.  <br>
<br>
After all this time I have now come full circle - back to where I started in Everquest.  Naleena is now almost 41 and I have found I am quite fond of this Magician (bordering on addicted).  She is quite amazing! The versatility is wonderful!<br>
<br>
My husband also plays Eq and his 58 warrior is now gathering dust because he has become addicted to a stumpy little dorf paladin...well what choice did he have? <br>
His cleric ran off to be a Magician! All clerics should be so lucky!<br>
<br>
As far as questions or issues, my biggest issue right now has to be spell research.  Necro words seem to drop like Rain<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rollin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/roll.gif ALT=":rollin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    while Magician words seem rare. But overall I'm working through it.<br>
<br>
Reading the recent posts here I see I have MUCH to learn...I did not even notice the Bolt had no graphic.  I just aimed and fired and if it did not land I moved a little and tried again <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :x --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/sick.gif ALT=":x"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->     And I try not to take resists too personally.<br>
<br>
Lady Naleena<br>
7th Hammer<br>
