<br>
Mages pre 50 and outside of raids are a holy terror. Often you will outdamage everyone else in the group easily, and your pet by itself will outdamage most tanks.<br>
<br>
Do not be afraid to experement. most mages i see use either earth pets, or epics.  they give up on the rest because they like the tanking ability. This is a bad thing. Pets like monster summoning, and decoy are absolutly gross, and have situations where tehy are more powerful than anything else.  Even the stupid post 50 fire pets do have a use.<br>
<br>
play with weapons too. some of those items that hit page 50 as soon as you get them have nice uses for pulling etc. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=barmodius>Barmodius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 41<br> <font color=#333333>(1/29/03 5:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8633.topic&index=14>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Newcomer to Magician's Tower</span><hr size=1> Resist gear?  Heh.  My first raid was a couple weeks ago in ToFS, so I went out before hand and blew a couple hundred plat on a few things, but not enough, because I did not resist anything that night.  No deaths, but I came close a couple times.<br>
